main event: A witness observed a bright white light in the sky over Colorado Springs, Colorado for approximately 5 minutes on November 8, 1966.
interesting points: The light appeared to be larger and brighter than any of the stars in the sky.
Occasionally, the light would dim slightly and then return to its normal brightness.
The light remained visible for approximately 10 to 15 minutes, at which time it suddenly disappeared from view.
There were no clouds in the sky at the time of the observation, and the visibility was excellent.
The object did not resemble any known aircraft or celestial body, and was classified as an unidentified flying object.
sighted object: bright white light in the sky
